posts.body:
There already exists an /r9k/ board, though it was created before the massive spam.
Can you see it?

I know this might be a minor nuisance, but I really like using the "Recent Posts" system from the homepage. The problem is that boards that don't have any traffic will be ignored by those that already have traffic (ie: /pol/ posts overshadow all the other boards)
It may sound stupid, but think about this. A system that allows you to see multiple lists of recent posts that can be modified (example: a list for all the recent posts on /pol/, and a list for all the recent posts on all the zite)
This will encourage anons to look for each other and their posts will be more relevant due to having more exposition.
